  95:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   *** Callback registration ***
  96:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   =============================================
  97:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
  98:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   The compilation define  USE_HAL_ETH_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
  99:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 100:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   Use Function HAL_ETH_RegisterCallback() to register an interrupt callback.
 101:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 102:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   Function HAL_ETH_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
 103:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) TxCpltCallback   : Tx Complete Callback.
 104:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) RxCpltCallback   : Rx Complete Callback.
 105:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback    : Error Callback.
 106:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) PMTCallback      : Power Management Callback
 107:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) EEECallback      : EEE Callback.
 108:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) WakeUpCallback   : Wake UP Callback
 109:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback  : MspInit Callback.
 110:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback: MspDeInit Callback.
 111:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 112:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 113:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   and a pointer to the user callback function.
 114:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 115:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks RxAllocateCallback use dedicated register callbacks:
 116:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_RegisterRxAllocateCallback().
 117:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 118:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks RxLinkCallback use dedicated register callbacks:
 119:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_RegisterRxLinkCallback().
 120:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 121:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks TxFreeCallback use dedicated register callbacks:
 122:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_RegisterTxFreeCallback().
 123:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 124:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks TxPtpCallback use dedicated register callbacks:
 125:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_RegisterTxPtpCallback().
 126:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 127:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   Use function HAL_ETH_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 128:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   weak function.
 129:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   HAL_ETH_UnRegisterCallback takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 130:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   and the Callback ID.
 131:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   This function allows to reset following callbacks:
 132:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) TxCpltCallback   : Tx Complete Callback.
 133:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) RxCpltCallback   : Rx Complete Callback.
 134:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback    : Error Callback.
 135:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) PMTCallback      : Power Management Callback
 136:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) EEECallback      : EEE Callback.
 137:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) WakeUpCallback   : Wake UP Callback
 138:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback  : MspInit Callback.
 139:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback: MspDeInit Callback.
 140:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 141:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks RxAllocateCallback use dedicated unregister callbacks:
 142:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_UnRegisterRxAllocateCallback().
 143:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 144:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks RxLinkCallback use dedicated unregister callbacks:
ARM GAS  C:\Users\hh\AppData\Local\Temp\ccAaxJWD.s 			page 4


 145:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_UnRegisterRxLinkCallback().
 146:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 147:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks TxFreeCallback use dedicated unregister callbacks:
 148:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_UnRegisterTxFreeCallback().
 149:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 150:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks TxPtpCallback use dedicated unregister callbacks:
 151:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_UnRegisterTxPtpCallback().
 152:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 153:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   By default, after the HAL_ETH_Init and when the state is HAL_ETH_STATE_RESET
 154:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 155:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   examples HAL_ETH_TxCpltCallback(), HAL_ETH_RxCpltCallback().
 156:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are
 157:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   reset to the legacy weak function in the HAL_ETH_Init/ HAL_ETH_DeInit only when
 158:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 159:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   if not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_ETH_Init/ HAL_ETH_DeInit
 160:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand)
 161:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 162:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_ETH_STATE_READY state only.
 163:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit that can be registered/unregistered
 164:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   in HAL_ETH_STATE_READY or HAL_ETH_STATE_RESET state,
 165:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 166:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 167:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   using HAL_ETH_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_ETH_DeInit
 168:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   or HAL_ETH_Init function.
 169:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 170:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   When The compilation define USE_HAL_ETH_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 171:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   not defined, the callback registration feature is not available and all callbacks
 172:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   are set to the corresponding weak functions.
